1
00:00:00,740 --> 00:00:02,600
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:08,710
The battle between the Alliance and Oracion 
Seis over Nirvana has finally come to an end!

3
00:00:08,710 --> 00:00:14,200
But waiting for us at the end were 
a number of tearful farewells...

4
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:53,330
Master Hades?

5
00:01:54,230 --> 00:01:56,230
Perhaps you are aware...

6
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:58,190
About what, Ultear?

7
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:05,110
That the Alliance has defeated 
Oracion Seis, and destroyed Nirvana.

8
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:08,020
Yes, impressive indeed.

9
00:02:08,410 --> 00:02:10,830
But our goal is...

10
00:02:10,830 --> 00:02:11,710
Yes.

11
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:15,350
To locate and obtain the 
keys to resurrecting Zeref.

12
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:19,090
It doesn't matter whether Nirvana 
is in the picture or not.

13
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:21,100
However...

14
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:23,450
However, what?

15
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:28,210
Lately, I have a feeling that 
something far greater is coming...

16
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:32,670
Some great disruption that will 
turn the world on its head.

17
00:02:33,890 --> 00:02:35,630
That's rare, from you.

18
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,760
Are you nervous?

19
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:40,720
On the contrary, I'm looking forward to it.

20
00:02:46,180 --> 00:02:49,600
Ah! Swaying in the sea breeze feels so nice!

21
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,250
Isn't this great, Natsu?

22
00:02:53,220 --> 00:02:56,310
Transportation is a wonderful thing!

23
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:58,760
The Troia will wear off soon, you know!

24
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:02,990
Troia is magic that cures motion sickness!

25
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:06,770
Cast it again!

26
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:10,540
If you do it over and over again, 
it'll get less effective.

27
00:03:10,540 --> 00:03:12,740
Just leave him be.

28
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:18,570
Carla, you and Wendy are really 
coming with us to Fairy Tale, huh?

29
00:03:18,570 --> 00:03:22,720
I'm just coming along because 
Wendy said she was going to.

30
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:24,270
I can't wait!

31
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:25,850
Fairy Tail!

32
00:03:30,990 --> 00:03:32,470
Call of the Dragon!

33
00:03:36,870 --> 00:03:41,210
The battle over, we each 
returned to our own guilds.

34
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,320
Men!

35
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:47,650
Until the next wonderful 
parfum, Erza-san, Lucy-san!

36
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,200
Come hang out at our place next time, 'kay?

37
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,290
We'll present you with the ultimate night...

38
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:56,340
Give my regards to Master Makarov!

39
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:58,920
Grey, do something about 
that stripping fetish.

40
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:01,030
I don't wanna hear that from you!

41
00:04:01,270 --> 00:04:04,640
Um... Should we just let this go by?

42
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:07,200
G-Go back already.

43
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:09,200
It's not like I'll be lonely or anything.

44
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,310
Sherry!

45
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,090
Ren!

46
00:04:11,090 --> 00:04:13,140
They llllike each other!

47
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:17,310
Back to our own guilds...

48
00:04:20,790 --> 00:04:24,620
And in my hands are three new keys.

49
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:28,850
The contract has been broken 
now that Angel's been caught.

50
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:29,910
Yup, yup.

51
00:04:29,910 --> 00:04:31,250
We are!

52
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:36,310
So we want <i>you</i> to be our new owner!

53
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:37,230
Yeah!

54
00:04:37,230 --> 00:04:38,840
Maybe we're asking too much?

55
00:04:40,210 --> 00:04:44,380
Three more friends from the 12 
Zodiac Gates, just like that...

56
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:46,210
Friends?

57
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:49,990
We're just tools for you to use. We?

58
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:53,210
Well, I've decided not to think like that.

59
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:55,140
You all look like people, right?

60
00:04:55,650 --> 00:04:59,160
I'm against treating you like objects.

61
00:05:01,090 --> 00:05:03,520
We're happy to be with you, Owner!

62
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:05,670
Yup!

63
00:05:05,670 --> 00:05:07,360
And I'm happy to have you!

64
00:05:07,360 --> 00:05:10,260
Scorpio, Aries, Gemini!

65
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:15,210
Mother... I've gained a 
lot more precious friends!

66
00:05:16,870 --> 00:05:22,490
And so, that's why I've invited 
Wendy and Carla to join Fairy Tail.

67
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,050
It's a pleasure!

68
00:05:25,050 --> 00:05:26,570
So cute!

69
00:05:26,570 --> 00:05:27,910
There's a girl Happy!

70
00:05:27,910 --> 00:05:28,930
How old are you, Miss?

71
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:31,430
Welcome back, everyone.

72
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:32,640
Master...

73
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,730
Excellent work.

74
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:41,250
This area should be 
peaceful now, for a while.

75
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:45,920
And of course, I bid Wendy 
and Carla a hearty welcome!

76
00:05:47,820 --> 00:05:49,610
Lu-chan, welcome back!

77
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:50,950
Levy-chan!

78
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:52,440
Lu-chan!

79
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:55,070
Oh, you... Always making a fuss...

80
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:57,090
I'm impressed they're all okay.

81
00:05:57,090 --> 00:06:00,310
Lucy's getting more and 
more out of our league...

82
00:06:01,670 --> 00:06:03,700
Ah, Gray-sama!

83
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:06,130
Juvia was so very, very worried!

84
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:08,540
Juvia's eyes pour with tears!

85
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:09,950
Grey, stop her!

86
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,240
I'm drowning!

87
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:12,550
Why me?!

88
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:18,000
And then there was this 
snake flying in the sky!

89
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,250
Snakes can't fly!

90
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:21,880
It's not like they're a man!

91
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:22,980
Man?

92
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,300
How do you do? I'm Mirajane.

93
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,260
Ooh!

94
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,520
Isn't it wonderful, Carla?

95
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,620
This is the real Mirajane-san!

96
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:37,200
I bet that Carla is the same as Happy, 
but what kind of magic do you use, Wendy?

97
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,580
What? Lumping me in with the he-cat?!

98
00:06:41,230 --> 00:06:44,330
I use Sky Magic.

99
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:46,800
I am the Sky Dragon Slayer.

100
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,900
Maybe they don't believe me...

101
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:58,570
Whoa, awesome!!

102
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:01,690
A Dragon Slayer!

103
00:07:01,690 --> 00:07:03,280
Wow!

104
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:04,790
The same as Natsu!

105
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:09,030
With Gajeel, that means our 
guild has three Dragon Slayers!

106
00:07:09,030 --> 00:07:11,410
Even though it's such rare magic!

107
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,910
C-Cat...

108
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,290
W-Why?

109
00:07:26,580 --> 00:07:28,730
We're all Dragon Slayers, and yet...

110
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,860
Why am I the only one without a cat?

111
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,240
Today we're having a celebration!

112
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:38,600
A party to welcome Wendy and Carla!

113
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:43,190
Live it up! Live it up!

114
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:45,310
Oh yeah! I'm gettin' fired up!

115
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:47,470
My clothes!

116
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:49,150
That's the spirit, Lucy!

117
00:07:49,150 --> 00:07:51,550
Gray-sama, you didn't 
cheat or anything, right?

118
00:07:51,550 --> 00:07:53,520
W-What's with her?

119
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:56,110
Carla, do you want my fish?

120
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,470
Absolutely not.

121
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:07,150
This place sure is fun, Carla.

122
00:08:07,150 --> 00:08:08,800
Not really my style.

123
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:33,110
Is there a request that strikes your fancy?

124
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:35,450
There are just so many.

125
00:08:35,730 --> 00:08:36,940
Yes.

126
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:41,200
It might be difficult to go on 
your own for your first job.

127
00:08:41,780 --> 00:08:45,210
I think it'd be a good idea to go with 
someone else as an assistant, first.

128
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:48,540
Although you'll only receive 
a portion of the reward.

129
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:52,520
Assistant?

130
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:55,470
Sure, but for these bunch?

131
00:09:00,150 --> 00:09:01,200
Rejected.

132
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:04,500
Did Wendy decide on a job?

133
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:09,220
No. She said she decided to 
go with someone else at first.

134
00:09:09,220 --> 00:09:13,330
Come to think of it, you went with 
Natsu on your first job, Lu-chan.

135
00:09:13,330 --> 00:09:17,740
And thanks to that, I've been put in 
situations where even infinite lives wouldn't be enough.

136
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:19,710
It sounds like a lot of fun, though.

137
00:09:19,710 --> 00:09:20,700
Um...

138
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:26,240
It's already been a week 
since I came to Fairy Tail.

139
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,880
So I was thinking I should do 
my first job pretty soon...

140
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,630
Then come with Shadow Gear!

141
00:09:32,630 --> 00:09:34,800
If you're going to, then how about with us?

142
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:39,470
Huh? But you just said that 
you never had enough lives...

143
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:43,040
Why don't you take turns then?

144
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:43,960
Sure!

145
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,830
That's a plan!

146
00:09:44,830 --> 00:09:46,400
Then, who goes first?

147
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:52,500
Natsu!

148
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:54,940
What is it?

149
00:09:55,590 --> 00:09:56,690
Gray...

150
00:09:57,120 --> 00:10:00,430
Now that I think about it, I 
haven't seen you for a few days.

151
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:04,030
Gray-sama, what's the matter?

152
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:08,040
I heard a crazy story, Natsu.

153
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,620
What?

154
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:16,210
Somebody outside the city 
says she's seen a dragon.

155
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:23,280
That's some incredible info, Natsu.

156
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,240
Yeah.

157
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:27,390
Dragon? Is it Igneel?

158
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:31,210
I don't know those details.

159
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,870
Did you meet the person who saw the dragon?

160
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:36,640
No.

161
00:10:36,900 --> 00:10:38,580
I just heard the rumors going around town.

162
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:43,470
Someone named "Daphne" talks like 
she knows all about dragons.

163
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,830
It's not just that she's seen one.

164
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:49,400
It sounds like she actually <i>met</i> one recently.

165
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,370
Really?

166
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,210
That's the truth, right?

167
00:10:53,050 --> 00:10:55,550
It might pay to find out for sure.

168
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:57,370
Where is she?

169
00:10:57,370 --> 00:11:01,090
In the wilderness to the 
west, at an Inn named "Rise".

170
00:11:01,450 --> 00:11:02,690
All right!

171
00:11:02,690 --> 00:11:03,800
Let's go, Happy.

172
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:04,920
Aye, sir!

173
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:07,080
I'll go, too!

174
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:10,140
That dragon might be Grandine!

175
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:11,980
Then let's check it out.

176
00:11:12,410 --> 00:11:13,600
You comin' too?

177
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,500
No way.

178
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:17,710
It's obviously a sham.

179
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:19,900
How can you know that?

180
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:24,750
And how many times have you 
said that and gotten tricked?

181
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:29,410
Stories about dragons are for luring people!

182
00:11:29,410 --> 00:11:31,360
You're being used!

183
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:33,380
Try learning a little.

184
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:36,520
You want to see yours too, right?

185
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:37,710
You want to see Metalicana!

186
00:11:37,710 --> 00:11:39,840
And then what?

187
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:43,310
He just disappeared without sayin' nothing.

188
00:11:43,310 --> 00:11:45,140
I don't care one bit!

189
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:47,400
Gajeel-san...

190
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:51,140
Well, he's like that, but 
he really misses him.

191
00:11:51,140 --> 00:11:52,640
I think so, too.

192
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:55,820
Let's go, Wendy.

193
00:11:55,820 --> 00:11:56,770
Right!

194
00:11:57,290 --> 00:11:59,960
I hope it's Grandine, Carla!

195
00:12:00,990 --> 00:12:04,910
But I think you shouldn't get your hopes up.

196
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:08,120
Thanks for the decent tip.

197
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:10,120
My pleasure.

198
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,830
I'd like this delivered.

199
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:34,190
Well, you're choosing 
another pretty cake today.

200
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:37,620
Yes. We have a cute new recruit, after all.

201
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:39,410
I was thinking of getting it for her.

202
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:42,390
And so you chose it to suit her, I see...

203
00:12:42,390 --> 00:12:43,610
Indeed.

204
00:12:43,940 --> 00:12:45,550
Can you handle 50 of them?

205
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:46,410
Oh?

206
00:12:46,410 --> 00:12:48,590
You have 50 newcomers?

207
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:51,430
49 of them are for myself.

208
00:12:53,380 --> 00:12:56,210
C-Come again!

209
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:17,730
Requip?

210
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:36,680
I can't... sense it anymore.

211
00:13:41,330 --> 00:13:43,680
This is the traveler's inn, Rise.

212
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:45,680
Kind of beat-up.

213
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:56,480
No one is here.

214
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,440
There shouldn't be.

215
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,540
What's this?

216
00:14:00,540 --> 00:14:03,940
It's a fully-automatic lacrima-based 
inn management system.

217
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:08,520
Check-in, check-out... This little 
thing takes care of it all.

218
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:11,460
So that's why there's no staff!

219
00:14:11,460 --> 00:14:15,580
No staff, sure. But I don't 
see any customers either.

220
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:18,070
Damn that Gray... It was a fake!

221
00:14:18,070 --> 00:14:20,770
It's too soon to decide that.

222
00:14:20,770 --> 00:14:22,940
Someone might be here.

223
00:14:22,940 --> 00:14:26,260
Why don't we check each room individually?

224
00:14:26,550 --> 00:14:27,940
Okay...

225
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:29,920
Let's all split up.

226
00:14:31,190 --> 00:14:32,370
Hey!

227
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:34,900
Excuse me!

228
00:14:40,540 --> 00:14:41,910
You didn't see that.

229
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:43,690
Cute...

230
00:14:44,710 --> 00:14:47,990
Sheesh, what's with this place?

231
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:51,450
So far, nobody's home.

232
00:14:51,670 --> 00:14:53,450
This is the last place to check.

233
00:14:53,880 --> 00:14:56,980
And this was the most suspicious 
place by far anyway.

234
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:58,830
What the hell are they thinking?

235
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:01,050
Hey! Anyone there?

236
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:02,990
Yes-yes.

237
00:15:02,990 --> 00:15:04,000
Someone's there!

238
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,270
Open up!

239
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:06,710
Are you this Daphne person?

240
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:13,690
Yes-yes. I am Daphne-san, and...?

241
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:17,560
I-I'd like to talk with you.

242
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:20,400
Yes-yes-yes! Talk, yes? Talk!

243
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,690
Could it be? Even if it 
isn't! You're a customer!

244
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:24,690
Come in, come in, come in, please!

245
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:26,650
Yes-yes-yes-yes!

246
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:29,320
What's going on?

247
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,730
Yes-yes-yes-yes.

248
00:15:33,220 --> 00:15:36,780
I travel from place to place, the master 
of spreading beauty around the land!

249
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:38,910
I am named Daphne!

250
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:46,140
No, not "B" as in "beat up"! "B" as in 
"beautiful", "B" as in "beauty", "B" as in "babealicious"!

251
00:15:46,140 --> 00:15:47,500
Yes-yes-yes-yes!

252
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,520
And what am I selling, you ask?

253
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,000
The diet food of your wildest dreams!

254
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:54,300
I call it Metamo-chan!

255
00:15:54,300 --> 00:15:55,700
Metabo-chan?

256
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:57,550
Uh...

257
00:15:57,550 --> 00:15:58,560
Yes-yes...

258
00:15:58,810 --> 00:15:59,510
You there!

259
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:01,820
Please be careful to say the name properly!

260
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:03,950
No, not Metabo-chan! Metamo-chan!

261
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:07,270
I created it after long, 
long years of research!

262
00:16:07,270 --> 00:16:09,050
It is truly a miraculous food product!

263
00:16:09,050 --> 00:16:09,560
Listen to me!

264
00:16:09,560 --> 00:16:14,290
Take the detoxifying bounty of the ocean and 
pickle it for 3 days and nights in secret medicine,

265
00:16:14,290 --> 00:16:16,690
then dry them out under 
the sun for another week.

266
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:19,080
And what do you have...? You!

267
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:22,100
The diet food of your wildest 
dreams, Metamo-chan!

268
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:23,200
Yes-yes!

269
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,190
You said it properly this time!

270
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:28,800
I'll give you a sample since you 
made me so happy, little kitty.

271
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,410
But I'm not overweight...

272
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:32,630
Yes-yes, it's quite delicious!

273
00:16:32,870 --> 00:16:35,320
Just one bite and your skin will shine!

274
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,140
Another bite and your indigestion is gone!

275
00:16:37,140 --> 00:16:38,210
Yes-yes...

276
00:16:38,210 --> 00:16:39,260
Are you two brother and sister?

277
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:43,950
Eat up, boys and girls and 
kitties! Eat my Metamo-chan!

278
00:16:44,580 --> 00:16:48,810
Just look at how effective it 
is in this before-and-after!

279
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:50,080
Wow!

280
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:51,410
It's super-effective!

281
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:53,990
Hey! What are you so impressed by?

282
00:16:53,990 --> 00:16:58,640
Now then, let me read the opinions 
of a few satisfied customers.

283
00:16:58,640 --> 00:17:01,770
First, from a Janruka-san who lives in Onibus:

284
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:03,990
Ever since I've started eating 
them, I've seen amazing results!

285
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:06,730
I reached my goal weight in only ten days!

286
00:17:06,390 --> 00:17:07,580
Uh, about my...

287
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:10,480
No diet magic ever worked, 
but Metamo-chan is wonderful!

288
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,070
Hold it!

289
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:16,140
Yes-yes. I have quite a lot 
more satisfied customers.

290
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:18,340
Stop saying "yes-yes"!

291
00:17:18,340 --> 00:17:20,790
I didn't come here to talk about diet pills!

292
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:22,460
Yes-yes! They aren't pills!

293
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:24,490
I'm talking about Metamo-chan!

294
00:17:24,490 --> 00:17:26,020
I want to talk about Dragons!

295
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:27,960
Yes-yes... Dragons, is it?

296
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,430
Sogladyouasked!

297
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:32,090
Even dragons can lose 
weight with Metamo-chan!

298
00:17:32,090 --> 00:17:33,040
That's how amazing it is!

299
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:35,090
Whatever! Just listen to me!

300
00:17:35,090 --> 00:17:37,030
I am a Dragon Slayer!

301
00:17:37,820 --> 00:17:42,010
I'm searching for a dragon named 
Igneel that disappeared 7 years ago.

302
00:17:42,010 --> 00:17:44,990
And she's searching for one named Grandine.

303
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:53,140
If you've met with one, please tell us which 
one, where you met, and when you met them.

304
00:17:58,330 --> 00:18:00,590
Something that could requip?

305
00:18:01,050 --> 00:18:04,590
Of course, there are others who 
can use requip-style magic.

306
00:18:05,090 --> 00:18:10,100
But what worries me is the smell of 
the one who attacked me suddenly.

307
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,450
The smell?

308
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:14,290
It was the smell of a beast.

309
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:17,690
And I didn't sense human breathing...

310
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:21,780
There might be some weird group at it again.

311
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,890
Then they will show themselves eventually.

312
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:26,700
We should not fret.

313
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:29,140
So, just leave things as they are?

314
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:33,510
We should take precautions, but it is 
not something to worry yourself over.

315
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:38,340
If it wants to do battle with 
you, it will appear again.

316
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:39,550
Right.

317
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:42,280
I'll be careful too, Erza.

318
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,430
Gray, Natsu... You two should...

319
00:18:44,430 --> 00:18:46,240
Huh? Where's Gray?

320
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:52,720
Gray-sama went off somewhere 
and didn't tell me!

321
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:54,200
For a job?

322
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,790
I don't know...

323
00:18:58,530 --> 00:19:00,780
You heard I met a dragon then?

324
00:19:01,020 --> 00:19:03,110
That was a lie to help sales!

325
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:04,470
Yes-yes...

326
00:19:04,470 --> 00:19:05,550
A lie?

327
00:19:05,550 --> 00:19:06,600
Aww...

328
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,220
Gajeel was spot on!

329
00:19:08,220 --> 00:19:10,370
I figured as much.

330
00:19:10,370 --> 00:19:11,720
Yes-yes.

331
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:16,420
I mean, if I said that Metamo-chan had 
powder ground from the scales of a dragon,

332
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:17,920
the sales would skyrocket!

333
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,280
Scales?

334
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:20,880
Yes-yes, but of course it's a lie.

335
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:23,020
Where could I get dragon scales, right?

336
00:19:23,020 --> 00:19:25,240
You're a fraud!

337
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,390
Oh?

338
00:19:26,390 --> 00:19:28,440
But my creations are perfect.

339
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:30,020
Who the hell are you?

340
00:19:30,020 --> 00:19:31,050
Yes-yes...

341
00:19:31,050 --> 00:19:34,450
Everyone's a satisfied customer, 
and will you be too, Mr. Dragon.

342
00:19:34,450 --> 00:19:36,060
I've had enough of you!

343
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:37,200
We're leaving!

344
00:19:42,150 --> 00:19:43,320
What the heck?

345
00:19:44,620 --> 00:19:46,530
The floor's gone!

346
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:48,450
What's the meaning of this?

347
00:19:48,450 --> 00:19:51,290
You are birds in a cage.

348
00:19:51,290 --> 00:19:53,440
This ain't nothin'!

349
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:56,520
Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon!

350
00:19:58,500 --> 00:19:59,530
Natsu-san!

351
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:00,550
Are you okay?

352
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:02,330
This is a magic barrier...

353
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:04,010
Are you a wizard?

354
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,120
Yes-yes...

355
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:07,680
Lovely flames you have there.

356
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,840
The Salamander, indeed...

357
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:12,950
She's acting differently.

358
00:20:12,950 --> 00:20:13,690
Yes-yes.

359
00:20:13,690 --> 00:20:18,580
I've been waiting for a customer 
like you... A Dragon Slayer!

360
00:20:18,580 --> 00:20:19,270
Oh, yeah?

361
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:21,880
Yes-yes-yes... You'll understand soon.

362
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,040
Calm down.

363
00:20:23,040 --> 00:20:23,970
How about one?

364
00:20:23,970 --> 00:20:25,160
I don't want any!

365
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,510
Strawberry flavor no good?

366
00:20:26,510 --> 00:20:28,510
How about wasabi flavor?

367
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:30,100
I said I don't want any!

368
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:31,370
The outside world is gone...

369
00:20:31,370 --> 00:20:33,930
We're completely trapped...

370
00:20:33,930 --> 00:20:35,190
Yes-yes-yes-yes...

371
00:20:35,190 --> 00:20:36,990
Quite impressive magic, don't you think?

372
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,090
I'll blast this magic to smithereens!

373
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:45,510
Ice?

374
00:20:49,050 --> 00:20:50,100
Gray!

375
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:55,100
Well, look at you, Natsu.

376
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,380
Gray-san!

377
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:59,270
Where did you come in from, Gray?

378
00:20:59,270 --> 00:21:00,660
Hey,Gray!

379
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:02,900
This info you got was a sham!

380
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:05,200
There's something wrong 
with this Daphne chick.

381
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,870
It wasn't a sham.

382
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,570
Good enough?

383
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:13,970
Yes-yes-yes-yes.

384
00:21:13,970 --> 00:21:17,100
Welcome, Gray Fullbuster.

385
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:18,790
You're...

386
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,750
You know each other?

387
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:26,400
Ooh, she llllikes him!

388
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,730
Gray, what's the meaning of this?

389
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:33,580
Natsu... We've gone at it a whole 
bunch of times, haven't we?

390
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:39,770
I was thinking... Maybe it's time we 
finally settled this, once and for all.

391
00:21:39,770 --> 00:21:41,590
What the hell are you saying?

392
00:21:41,590 --> 00:21:45,710
Until now, I've been bringing 
myself down to your level.

393
00:21:45,710 --> 00:21:48,410
But I'm sick of it.

394
00:21:48,730 --> 00:21:51,130
I'm going to do things my own way.

395
00:21:51,550 --> 00:21:53,870
I'm not sticking with you any more.

396
00:21:53,870 --> 00:21:55,090
Gray...

397
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:57,840
Yes-yes, just as you heard.

398
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:00,800
Gray Fullbuster is mine.

399
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:03,610
I want that Dragon Slayer.

400
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:05,530
Crush him.

401
00:22:06,780 --> 00:22:08,210
Gray, you're acting weird!

402
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:12,430
You're the one that's weird.

403
00:22:13,660 --> 00:22:16,400
Later, Natsu!

404
00:23:55,650 --> 00:23:58,090
Which one of you is stronger? You or Gray?

405
00:23:58,090 --> 00:23:59,200
Me, obviously!

406
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,830
I'll never lose to that pervert!

407
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:06,540
Well, Gray just said he'll 
never lose to that hothead!

408
00:24:06,540 --> 00:24:07,540
Oh, yeah?!

409
00:24:07,540 --> 00:24:09,920
That droopy-eyed, naked...

410
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,510
That droopy-eyed, naked, 
walking giant-boxers bastard!

411
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:13,910
Waaaay too long.

412
00:24:14,150 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Natsu vs. Gray!

413
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:18,680
Longer isn't better, you know!

414
00:24:18,930 --> 00:24:20,560
You have to make it more compact!

415
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:21,790
Then let's just go with "pervert"!

416
00:24:22,020 --> 00:24:24,560
Blunt, but effective.

